# DevOps Cheat Sheet

## Git
- `git init`
- `git clone <repo>`
- `git status`
- `git add <file>`
- `git commit -m "message"`
- `git branch`
- `git checkout <branch>`
- `git checkout -b <new-branch>`
- `git merge <branch>`
- `git pull`
- `git push`
- `git log --oneline --graph --all`

## CI/CD
- Build: compile, test, package
- Test: unit, integration, e2e
- Deploy: staging, production
- Common tools: Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, CircleCI, Azure DevOps
- Pipeline stages: checkout -> build -> test -> package -> deploy
- Example YAML steps:
    - checkout code
    - install dependencies
    - run tests
    - build artifact
    - deploy artifact

## Containers
- `docker build -t <name>:<tag> .`
- `docker images`
- `docker run -d --name <container> <image>`
- `docker ps`
- `docker exec -it <container> /bin/sh`
- `docker logs <container>`
- `docker stop <container>`
- `docker rm <container>`
- `docker-compose up -d`
- Dockerfile basics:
    - `FROM`
    - `WORKDIR`
    - `COPY`
    - `RUN`
    - `EXPOSE`
    - `CMD` / `ENTRYPOINT`

## Kubernetes
- `kubectl get pods`
- `kubectl get svc`
- `kubectl get deployments`
- `kubectl apply -f <file>`
- `kubectl delete -f <file>`
- `kubectl describe pod <name>`
- `kubectl logs <pod>`
- `kubectl exec -it <pod> -- /bin/sh`

## Helm
- Helm charts: package manager for Kubernetes
- `helm create <chart>`
- `helm install <release> <chart>`
- `helm upgrade <release> <chart>`
- `helm list`
- `helm uninstall <release>`
- `helm repo add <name> <url>`
- `helm repo update`
- Chart structure: Chart.yaml, values.yaml, templates/

## ArgoCD
- GitOps tool for Kubernetes
- `argocd login <server>`
- `argocd app create <app> --repo <repo> --path <path> --dest-server <server> --dest-namespace <ns>`
- `argocd app get <app>`
- `argocd app sync <app>`
- `argocd app delete <app>`
- Sync policies: manual, auto
- Declarative config via YAML

## GitOps
- Practice of using Git as single source of truth for infrastructure and applications
- Principles: declarative, versioned, immutable, automated
- Tools: ArgoCD, Flux, Jenkins X
- Workflows: push to Git -> CI -> deploy via CD tool
- Benefits: auditability, rollback via Git, consistency

## Jenkins
- CI/CD server
- `jenkins-cli.jar` for CLI commands
- Pipeline syntax: Declarative vs Scripted
- Plugins: Git, Docker, Kubernetes
- Webhooks for triggers
- Blue Ocean for visual pipelines
- Master-agent architecture

## Infrastructure as Code
- Terraform: `.tf` files
    - `terraform init`
    - `terraform plan`
    - `terraform apply`
    - `terraform destroy`
- CloudFormation / ARM / Bicep
- Ansible:
    - `ansible-playbook playbook.yml`
    - inventory file
    - tasks, roles, handlers

## Monitoring & Logging
- Prometheus: metrics collection, alert rules
- Grafana: dashboards, panels
- ELK / EFK: Elasticsearch, Logstash/Fluentd, Kibana
- Alerts: PagerDuty, Opsgenie, Slack
- Health checks, uptime, error rates, latency

## Security & Compliance
- Secrets management: Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault
- IAM least privilege
- Static analysis: SAST, dependency scanning
- Container scanning
- Patch management
- Network security groups, firewalls

## Common Commands
- Linux:
    - `top`, `htop`
    - `df -h`
    - `du -sh ./*`
    - `ps aux | grep <process>`
    - `netstat -tulnp`
    - `ss -tulnp`
- Systemctl:
    - `systemctl status <service>`
    - `systemctl start <service>`
    - `systemctl stop <service>`
    - `systemctl enable <service>`

## Best Practices
- Automate everything
- Use version control for code and config
- Keep CI pipeline fast and reliable
- Maintain repeatable environments
- Deploy small, frequent changes
- Rollback strategy
- Use observability and metrics
- Enforce code review and testing

## Notes
- Keep scripts idempotent
- Use environment variables for config
- Avoid hard-coded secrets
- Document processes and runbooks